Sars expects scores of people to make their way to their branches and has opted to open on Saturdays as well. JOHANNESBURG As income tax return season comes to an end-the South African Revenue Services (Sars) has urged South African s to avoid the last minute rush.Sars spokesman Sandile Memela says the service expects scores of people to make their way to their branches, hence they've opted to open on Saturdays for the next two weekends.Over four million tax returns have already been filed this season.Memela says that only tax return filings will be prioritised to cater for everyone before 25 November. We expect an increase in the number of people who will be in a last minute rush to file their income tax returns. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)